        <H2>API documentation</H2>
        <table style="width:100%">
            <thead>
                <th>Endpoint</th>
                <th>Full url</th>
                <th>Description</th>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td>/api/v1</td>
                    <td>http://localhost:3000/api/v1</td>
                    <td>
                        This is the index url. the very first endpoint.
                        returns information about the author of api, and a welcome message.
                        <br>
                        {
                            success:true,
                            message:"welcome",
                        }
                    </td>
                </tr>

                <tr>
                        <td>/api/v1/apod</td>
                        <td>http://localhost:3000/api/v1/apod</td>
                        <td>
                            This api endpoint returns APODS results from NASAs API.
                            <br>
                            <code>
                                <strong>params:</strong><br>
                                date : year-month-day <br>
                                hd: Boolean <br>
                            </code>
                            <p>
                                a resource will be picked of the date provided. hd determines wether or not to send hd resource.
                            </p>
                            <strong>example</strong><br>
                            <code>
                                http://url/api/v1/apod?date=2018-10-18&hd=true
                            </code> <br>
                            <i>no parameters are given, defaults will be provided</i><br>
                            <code>
                                date : today <br>
                                hd   : false  

                            </code>
                        </td>
                    </tr>
               
            </tbody>
        </table>

        <br>
        <br>
        <H2>Status Codes</H2>
        <table style="width:100%">
            <thead>
                <th>Code</th>
                <th>Explanation</th>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td>200 ­ OK</td>
                    <td>Everything worked as expected.</td>
                    
                </tr>
                <tr>
                        <td>400 ­ Bad Request</td>
                        <td>The request was unacceptable, often due to missing a required parameter.</td>
                        
                </tr>
                <tr>
                        <td>404 ­ Not Found</td>
                        <td>The requested resource doesn’t exist</td>
                        
                </tr>
                <tr>
                        <td>500, 502, 503, 504 ­ Server Errors</td>
                        <td>Something went wrong on the API’s end. (These are rare.)</td>
                        
                </tr>

               
            </tbody>
        </table>


    </body>
